nodes.documentation:
@dev Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where
there is an account (an manager) that can be granted exclusive access to
specific functions.
 * By default, the manager account will be the one that deploys the contract. This
can later be changed with {transferManagement}.
 * This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier
`onlyManager`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to
the manager.
nodes.name: Manageable

nodes.documentation: @dev Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial manager.
@dev Returns the address of the current manager.
nodes.name: manager

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "Manageable: caller is not the manager"

arguments.value: Manageable: caller is not the manager

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Manageable: caller is not the manager"

nodes.documentation: @dev Throws if called by any account other than the manager.
nodes.name: onlyManager

nodes.documentation:
@dev Leaves the contract without manager. It will not be possible to call
`onlyManager` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current manager.
     * NOTE: Renouncing management will leave the contract without an manager,
thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the manager.
nodes.name: renounceManagement

nodes.documentation:
@dev Transfers management of the contract to a new account (`newManager`).
Can only be called by the current manager.
nodes.name: transferManagement

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "Manageable: new manager is the zero address"

arguments.value: Manageable: new manager is the zero address

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Manageable: new manager is the zero address"

nodes.documentation: @dev Transfers management of the contract to a new account (`newManager`).
